The 36 abducted people in Guga of Bakori LGA, Katsina State have regained their freedom after a month in bandits’ den. According to Alhaji Mahdi Danbinta Guga whose wife and daughter were among the victims, their release was after the payment of N21,000,000 ransom sourced by the Guga community.Their release was today around 6:00 pm. •A file photo of Mr Rano, the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) killed by gunmen who attacked Jibia town on February 8, 2022 Gunmen suspected to be bandits have killed a Divisional Police Officer (DPO) during an attack on Jibia town in Jibia Local Government Area of Katsina State. The slain… In "Top Stories" Some of the 26 girls, who were kidnapped from their village in Faskari local government area of Katsina state, have narrated their ordeal in the hands of abductors. The girls were abducted from their homes on October 13, and were eventually released on November 3. The details of their release… In "News" Was it not strange that the abduction of Kankara boys occurred on the day President Muhammadu Buhari arrived Daura, his hometown, in Katsina State, on a private visit? It is even more curious that the abductees were released on his birthday. Buhari last visited the state in December 2019, when… In "Opinion"